If a unanimous vote were carried in this House, the position of the dele- gates would be greatly strengthened, and it would hasten the‘consummation of the union so much desired by the Opposition. In all sincerity, my sole object is to obtain Confederation on ' the most favorable Terms, so that we may not, after the union is completed, be discontented, and forced to resort to immediate local taxation to relieve the pressing wants of the country. Under Contederation, we shall ﬁnd that our expenditure will increase year after year, while our Revenue will' remain stationary.
